Fig. 330
) in pale specimens that can be enlarged to eventually cover the entire synsclerite in dark specimens. Ventral part of T7+S7 with original S7 distinctly convex with somewhat sinuous lateral margins and separated laterally from T7 by very narrow membranous slit reaching to anterior nfth or sixth of synsclerite (
Fig. 331
